docs.abstract: The vote for Kristina Karamo, who resoundingly lost her bid for secretary of state last year, cements the party’s takeover by Trump loyalists.
docs.snippet: The vote for Kristina Karamo, who resoundingly lost her bid for secretary of state last year, cements the party’s takeover by Trump loyalists.
docs.lead_paragraph: LANSING, Mich. — Michigan Republicans on Saturday picked Kristina Karamo to lead the party in the battleground state, fully embracing an election-denying Trump acolyte after her failed bid for statewide office, one in which she unsuccessfully sued to throw out mail-in votes in Detroit and refused to concede.

headline.main: Michigan G.O.P. Installs Kristina Karamo, an Election Denier, as Leader
headline.print_headline: Michigan G.O.P. Installs Election Denier as Leader

docs.abstract: Voters are going to the polls today in the primary election for a swing seat on the state’s Supreme Court, with abortion rights, gerrymandered maps and more at stake.
docs.snippet: Voters are going to the polls today in the primary election for a swing seat on the state’s Supreme Court, with abortion rights, gerrymandered maps and more at stake.
docs.lead_paragraph: BELOIT, Wis. — It is a funny thing about American politics that for one night, the nation’s most important campaign of 2023 descended on Cheezhead Brewing, a tavern where about 50 Republicans gathered to discuss the Wisconsin Supreme Court race.

headline.main: What to Watch For in a Consequential Court Election in Wisconsin

docs.abstract: The presidential election this month in Africa’s most populous country is completely unpredictable. An unexpected third candidate with a huge youth following may upend decades of traditional politics.
docs.snippet: The presidential election this month in Africa’s most populous country is completely unpredictable. An unexpected third candidate with a huge youth following may upend decades of traditional politics.
docs.lead_paragraph: Nigerians go to the polls this week to choose a new president — one of the most important elections happening anywhere in the world this year. Nigeria is Africa’s most populous country, with about 220 million people, and what happens there reverberates across the continent and the globe.

headline.main: Nigerian Election 2023: What to Know, What Polling Shows
headline.print_headline: Why Nigeria’s Election Is So Crucial, and Unpredictable

docs.abstract: The do-over vote on Sunday is only the tip of the iceberg for a city some see as in crisis: short on housing, schools and efficient governance.
docs.snippet: The do-over vote on Sunday is only the tip of the iceberg for a city some see as in crisis: short on housing, schools and efficient governance.
docs.lead_paragraph: BERLIN — The city’s airport came in more than $4 billion over budget and nine years late. Then there is the chronic housing shortage, the overcrowded schools and the crumbling subway system. If all of that is not enough to dispel any notion that Berlin is a model of efficiency, then maybe this Sunday’s court-ordered repeat election is.

headline.main: Repeat Election in Berlin Speaks to the ‘Chaos’ Many Residents Feel
headline.print_headline: Do-Over Election Speaks to ‘Chaos’ Felt in Berlin

docs.abstract: Democrats have a good chance of winning a majority in the chamber after a month in which three vacancies have paralyzed it.
docs.snippet: Democrats have a good chance of winning a majority in the chamber after a month in which three vacancies have paralyzed it.
docs.lead_paragraph: For a month, the Pennsylvania legislature has been frozen by a handful of vacancies in the State House of Representatives that made the difference between Democratic and Republican control, and by representatives’ inability to agree on basic operating rules.

headline.main: 3 Special Elections Will Determine Control of the Pennsylvania House
headline.print_headline: Control of the Pennsylvania House Is Up for Grabs With 3 Special Elections

docs.abstract: A new law targets a party founded by an imprisoned former official of the neo-Nazi group Golden Dawn. But critics say its reach could be wider.
docs.snippet: A new law targets a party founded by an imprisoned former official of the neo-Nazi group Golden Dawn. But critics say its reach could be wider.
docs.lead_paragraph: Greece’s government has moved to block from Parliament an extreme-right party seen as a successor to the neo-Nazi group Golden Dawn, which shot to prominence a decade ago but was effectively banned after being declared a criminal organization.

headline.main: Greece Moves to Block Far-Right Party as Election Nears

docs.lead_paragraph: Newly disclosed messages and testimony from some of the biggest stars and most senior executives at Fox News revealed that they privately expressed disbelief about President Donald J. docs.abstract: Releasing the introduction and conclusion of a special grand jury report could shed light on the extent to which Mr. Trump and others might face legal jeopardy in the case.

docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — A Georgia judge said on Monday that he would disclose parts of a grand jury report later this week that details an investigation into election interference by former President Donald J. Trump and his allies, though he would keep the jury’s specific recommendations secret for now.

headline.main: Georgia Judge Will Release Parts of Report on Trump Election Inquiry
headline.print_headline: Georgia Judge to Release Part of Trump Grand Jury Report

docs.abstract: A furor is building among some survivors over the government’s handling of the crisis. “I have been voting for this government for 20 years,” said one. “I will never forgive them.”
docs.snippet: A furor is building among some survivors over the government’s handling of the crisis. “I have been voting for this government for 20 years,” said one. “I will never forgive them.”
docs.lead_paragraph: GAZIANTEP, Turkey — A powerful earthquake struck northwestern Turkey in 1999, killing more than 17,000 people, exposing government incompetence and fueling an economic crisis. Amid the turmoil, a young, charismatic politician rode a wave of public anger to become prime minister in 2003.

headline.main: Anger Over Quake Response Challenges Erdogan Ahead of Election
headline.print_headline: Quake Response Testing Erdogan As Survivors Express Frustration
